]]>
</programlisting>

<para>
  The <emphasis role="italic">initializing</emphasis> attribute reflects the status of the initialization of the <link
  linkend="ovvUnderlying">underlying</link> Windows dialog. The value of the attribute is
  <computeroutput>.true</computeroutput> prior to the creation of the underlying dialog and up to the point that the
  underlying dialog has finished its initialization. From that point on, its value is
  <computeroutput>.false</computeroutput>.
</para>
<variablelist>
  <varlistentry><term><emphasis role="bold">initializing get:</emphasis></term>
  <listitem>
  <para>
    The <emphasis role="italic">initializing</emphasis> attribute returns <computeroutput>.true</computeroutput> until
    the Windows dialog has completed its initialization. Afterwards, the attribute will always return
    <computeroutput>.false</computeroutput>
  </para>
  </listitem></varlistentry>
  <varlistentry><term><emphasis role="bold">initializing set:</emphasis></term>
  <listitem>
  <para>
    The ooDialog framework sets the <emphasis role="italic">initializing</emphasis> attribute internally to reflect the
